<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-MKh-Uf1wXyS-4Siar3osCw" name="Create_Goal_Model,_5eCkYG-yEd6zv6nlDL4ZGQ" guid="-MKh-Uf1wXyS-4Siar3osCw" authors="Brian Elvesæter (SINTEF), Andrey Sadovykh (SOFTEAM)" changeDate="2010-11-03T10:24:32.086+0100" changeDescription="0.5: Revised description according to SoaML methodology book chapter.|0.4: Revised description and categorization.|0.3: Updated steps.|0.2: Updated description.|0.1: Initial outline." version="0.5">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    The purpose of the BMM is to agree with the business stakeholders the business goals that will be met by implementing&#xD;
    the service-oriented architecture, so that a set of required high level business processes can be identified for&#xD;
    further analysis. BMM provides a scheme or structure for developing, communicating, and managing business plans in an&#xD;
    organized manner. In particular, the BMM supports the following:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
            It identifies factors that motivate the establishment of business plans.&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
            It identifies and defines the elements of business plans.&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
            It indicates how all these factors and elements inter-relate.&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    Among these elements you find business policies and business rule that provide governance for and guidance to the&#xD;
    business. Once produced and agreed, the BMM serves as a reference that ensures that a full assessment may be made of&#xD;
    all the business implications of any proposed changes to the service-oriented architecture.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    The specification of the goals and company’s motivations are defined in a business goals diagram. The goals can be&#xD;
    structured by applying containers within the BMM model. The containers contain one or more goals diagrams in which you&#xD;
    can define the goals and their relationships.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_Fr7iUqGhEeC1A-PuG6Rlow" name="1. Identify goals." guid="_Fr7iUqGhEeC1A-PuG6Rlow">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>Business goals are discovered by a&#xD;
    process of workshops&lt;/font>&lt;/font> &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&#xD;
    face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>and interviews involving relevant stakeholders. The BMM describes a loose&#xD;
    hierarchy&lt;/font>&lt;/font> &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>of goals of&#xD;
    the business within the particular area of concern, from the&lt;/font>&lt;/font> &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&#xD;
    face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>goals of a business stakeholder in developing a&#xD;
    product to the business goals met&lt;/font>&lt;/font> &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&#xD;
    face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>by the product or its users.&lt;/font>&lt;/font>&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Fr7iUaGhEeC1A-PuG6Rlow" name="2. Specify goals and their relationships." guid="_Fr7iUaGhEeC1A-PuG6Rlow">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>The goals are created as classes&#xD;
    containing motivation related information. The name is expressed in a natural language and has properties such&#xD;
    as:&lt;/font>&lt;/font>&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
            Name, e.g. &quot;Minimize Risk&quot;&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Scope, &quot; strategic|operational|relative&quot;, e.g. strategic&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        IsCorporate, &quot;true|false&quot;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Kind, &quot;Quantitative|Qualitative&quot;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Requested Satisfaction, &quot;hard|soft&quot;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Unit of Measurement&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Goal Value&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Current value&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Problems&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Source&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Text, textual description of the goal&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Describe elements using &quot;notes&quot;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>Relationships between goals can be&#xD;
    specified as:&lt;/font>&lt;/font>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &quot;part of&quot; link&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &quot;positive influence&quot; link&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &quot;negative influence&quot; link&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &quot;guarantee&quot; link&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &quot;measure&quot; link&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &quot;assigned&quot; link&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &quot;traceability&quot; link&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Fr7iU6GhEeC1A-PuG6Rlow" name="3. Perform goal analysis linking the goals to existing or potential new business processes." guid="_Fr7iU6GhEeC1A-PuG6Rlow">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>Goals may be thought of as high level&#xD;
    statements of the&lt;/font>&lt;/font> &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&#xD;
    face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>things that have to happen in a business, each expressed as an outcome, but&#xD;
    without&lt;/font>&lt;/font> &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>specifying the&#xD;
    ”how”. As goal analysis proceeds, the analyst describes an enabling&lt;/font>&lt;/font> &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&#xD;
    face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>behaviour as the means by which a higher level&#xD;
    outcome is to be achieved.&lt;/font>&lt;/font> &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&#xD;
    face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>Initially this is done through a brain-storming process. This results in a list of&#xD;
    enabling&lt;/font>&lt;/font> &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>behaviours&#xD;
    that is further refined and consolidated into a set of enabling&lt;/font>&lt;/font> &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&#xD;
    face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>behaviours that supports all the business goals.&#xD;
    This is the starting point for business&lt;/font>&lt;/font> &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&#xD;
    face=&quot;NimbusRomNo9L-Regu&quot;>process modelling in a BPMN tool.&lt;/font>&lt;/font>&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To identify and specify&amp;nbsp;business goals.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
